<!-- Section 3 — Founder Story -->
<section class="section-founder" id="founder">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-founder__grid">
      <div class="section-founder__image">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80" alt="Founder portrait" loading="lazy">
      </div>
      <div class="section-founder__content">
        <span class="section-founder__label">THE FOUNDER</span>
        <h2 class="section-founder__headline">A Door Changed Everything.</h2>
        <p>At six years old, he was adopted. New home, new name, new life — but every system he entered after that door treated him like a number. Foster care. Public school. Mental health services. All built around him, never with him.</p>
        <p>By the time the mental health crisis hit, the mandate was already forming: someone has to build the thing that doesn't exist yet. An organization that doesn't ask young people to be grateful for systems that fail them — one that puts them in charge of rewriting those systems entirely.</p>
        <p>Almost Human Group is that thing. It exists because one person got tired of almost being seen, almost being heard, almost being human in rooms that decided his future without asking his name.</p>
        <blockquote class="section-founder__quote">
          <p>"Children are not at the will of the education system. The education system is at the will of the children."</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 4 — Mission -->
<section class="section-mission" id="mission">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-mission__inner">
      <span class="section-mission__label">OUR MISSION</span>
      <h2 class="section-mission__headline">The Organized, Uncompromising Voice of the Next Generation.</h2>
      <p>We build programs, shape policy, and demand representation for children, teens, and young adults — particularly those in foster care, under-resourced schools, and broken systems. We do not wait. We do not ask nicely. We show up, and we do not leave.</p>
      <div class="section-mission__structure">
        <h3>Why a 501(c)(4)?</h3>
        <p>Because the problems facing the next generation are political. A 501(c)(3) can serve. A 501(c)(4) can serve <em>and</em> fight — lobbying legislators, endorsing policy, holding power accountable without apology.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Section 5 — Values -->
<section class="section-values" id="values">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-values__label">OUR VALUES</span>
    <h2 class="section-values__headline">What We Refuse to Negotiate.</h2>
    <div class="card-grid card-grid--five">
      <div class="card card--value">
        <span class="card__number">01</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Proximity Over Distance</h3>
        <p class="card__text">The people closest to the problem build the solution. No exceptions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--value">
        <span class="card__number">02</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Certainty Over Comfort</h3>
        <p class="card__text">We say what we mean. Ambiguity is a luxury the next generation cannot afford.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--value">
        <span class="card__number">03</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Structure Over Symbolism</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Marches fade. Infrastructure remains. We build things that outlast us.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--value">
        <span class="card__number">04</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Urgency Without Panic</h3>
        <p class="card__text">We move fast because lives depend on it — but we move with precision, not chaos.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card card--value">
        <span class="card__number">05</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Accountability by Name</h3>
        <p class="card__text">We name who is responsible. Systems don't fail — people in charge of systems fail.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

